-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-30/british-pound-near-two-month-low-versus-dollar-before-retail-sales-report.html
The pound was within one cent of
the least versus the dollar in almost two months before data
forecast to show an index of U.K. retail sales fell to a nine-
month low in March.  Britainâ€™s currency snapped a two-day decline against the
euro. The Confederation of British Industry index will drop to
minus two, the lowest since June, from six in February,
according to the median estimate  of nine economists surveyed by
Bloomberg News. The CBI is scheduled to publish the report at 11
a.m. in  London .  The pound was little changed at $1.6019 as of 7:21 a.m. in
London. It reached $1.5937 on March 28, the least since Jan. 31.
Sterling strengthened 0.2 percent to 87.93 pence per euro after
touching 88.36 pence yesterday, the weakest since Oct. 26. It
was 0.5 percent stronger at 132.74 yen.  Bank of England  policy maker  Paul Fisher  is scheduled to
